Mirrors the existing screenshot-quality enforcement onto the video: a new
core/video_evidence module + tests give analyze_video.py a real verdict, the
post-test-plan command and the /t3:e2e + /t3:e2e-review skills reject a video
whose opening frames are blank (the dead pre-roll defect), and an e2e_review
eval scenario pins the HOLD-on-blank-preroll behaviour. BLUEPRINT updated.

Recovered from an uncommitted worktree after an unplanned reboot.
